failoverTarget.description: Specifies if the replica is the failover target. If the field is set to `true` the replica will be designated as a failover replica. In case the primary instance fails, the replica instance will be promoted as the new primary instance. Specifically, the name must be 1-63 characters long and match the regular expression [a-z]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])?. Reserved for future use.

If this field is not specified when creating a new instance, NOT_REQUIRED is used. If this field is not specified when patching or updating an existing instance, it is left unchanged in the instance.
